WyjaÅnienia

Aby ustaliÄ, ktÃ³ry z wybranych modeli jest najlepszy, dokonano analizy modeli przy pomocy pakietu DALEX.

library(DALEX)
library(auditor)
library(Matrix)
library(xgboost)
library(gbm)
dane<-read.csv("fico_NAver3.csv",h=T, sep=",")
dane$RiskPerformance<-ifelse(dane$RiskPerformance=="Bad",1,0)
pred_glm<-function(model,newdata, type="terms"){
  predict(model,newdata=newdata,type="response")
}
pred_boost<-function(model,newdata){
  predict(model,newdata=newdata,n.trees=model$n.trees)
}


expl_glm<-explain(model_glm,data=dane[,-1],y=dane[,1],predict_function = pred_glm)
expl_xgb <- explain(model_xgboost, 
                         data = model_martix_train, 
                         y = dane$RiskPerformance, 
                         label = "xgboost")
expl_boost<-explain(model_gradient_boosting,data=dane[,-1],y=dane[,1],predict_function = pred_boost)
